// Adversarial: Anchor chip plants the breaker at its current position, activating a damage
// multiplier while stationary. Chaos 0.7 action probability drives rapid start/stop movement
// cycles — the breaker constantly crosses the plant/unplant threshold, toggling the anchor
// state machine at near-maximum frequency. Fortress layout's heavy cell armor extends the run
// duration across 8000 frames so the anchor state can cycle hundreds of times. The adversarial
// risk: if the plant timer is not properly reset when the breaker moves before the timer
// expires (interrupted plant), or if a double-unplant event fires two timer-cancel messages
// in the same frame, NoEntityLeaks fires for orphaned timer entities and BoltSpeedAccurate
// catches the multiplier state stuck in the "planted" value after unplant. BreakerInBounds
// ensures the Chrono breaker's position is not corrupted by rapid plant/unplant events.
// NoNaN guards against division-by-zero in the plant-timer normalisation path.
(
    breaker: "Chrono",
    layout: "Fortress",
    input: Chaos((action_prob: 0.7)),
    max_frames: 4000,
    disallowed_failures: [BoltInBounds, BoltSpeedAccurate, BreakerCountReasonable, BreakerInBounds, NoEntityLeaks, NoNaN],
    allowed_failures: None,
    debug_setup: None,
    allow_early_end: false,
    seed: 5171,
    chip_selections: ["Anchor"],
)
